snippet.textDisplay:
@Mac Clift We all need magnesium exposure, though.  ATP, the energy currency of the cell, does not work at all -- unless a magnesium is attached to it.  Every Mg-ATP dependent process and enzyme in the body is magnesium dependent.  3,751 protein types in the human body have mangesium specific receptors to optimize their functionality.  Hormone function depends on magnesium.
And it just so happens that magnesium regulates every facet of vitamin D metabolism.  Little known is the fact that the sun also breaks down retinol into retinoic acid -- the form usable by ATP7B to load copper into ceruloplasmin to manage all the oxidase enzymes (including cytochrome c oxidase in the electron transfer chain step right before Mg-ATP is made!) and to prevent both heavy metal iron and copper from going rogue and driving oxidative stress, inflammation, and the physiological effects that occur due to the oxidative stress and inflammation.
